Chairmen of All Progressives Congress(APC) and Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Messrs Ade Adetimehin and Fatai Adams have expressed hope of a better economic situations in the New Year. In separate statements made available to newsmen in Akure, the state capital, on Friday, the political chieftains noted that though the year 2020 was full of various challenges, they both hoped for better days. According to Adetimehin, the APC Caretaker Committee chairman, assured his party faithful of a robust new year, in terms of patronage and reward from a party, into which they have invested so much efforts, time and resources. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said: “All the leaders and members of the all progressives congress made me proud throughout the year 2020, in conducting themselves properly, and, more importantly, for supporting the party during the local government, and gubernatorial elections. “I want to assure them of a robust 2021. I promise to stand by them, and ensure they are adequately rewarded for their commitments and dedication to party affairs.” Ex-Lawmaker Fetes PDP Members, Distributes Palliatives 2021: Osun APC Promises All-Inclusive Governance Adams, in his statement, noted the people of the state like other states were exposed to “the crippling effects of covid-19 pandemic, depression in the economy, activities of herdsmen, kidnappers and other criminals and near total collapse of infrastructural facilities in the state. “The aftermath of EndSARS protests, to murder of prominent citizens in the state. but thank god, we have come to the end of a year that is like no other.” He, however, expressed hope of improved economic situations in the state, saying “According to King David in Psalms 30:5 “Weeping may endure for a night, but joy comes in the morning.” “We believe and pray that, in the year 2021, there shall be a new dawn for Ondo State in ge